('Ciaran McNeill', 'Ciaran', 'McNeill', 'General Manager | Luxury & Multi-Property Resort Operations | Pre-Opening Specialist | Phuket', 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/ciaran-mcneill-3179a933', 'ciaran-mcneill-3179a933', $${"about": "With over 20 years of international hospitality experience, I specialise in leading upscale resort operations, improving guest satisfaction, and delivering strong financial performance across complex resort environments.\n\nCurrently General Manager of Crest Resort & Pool Villas in Phuket, overseeing the operations of a 144-room luxury hillside resort including 34 private pool villas, multiple restaurants, spa facilities and multi-department teams. My focus is on strengthening service culture, improving operational efficiency, and driving revenue growth through guest experience innovation and strategic F&B development.\n\nRecent operational results include:\n\n• Increasing total resort revenue by over 8% year-on-year while improving ADR and occupancy\n• Growing room revenue by more than 12% through operational and pricing optimisation\n• Improving Booking.com guest score from 8.1 to 8.6\n• Increasing TripAdvisor rating from 4.6 to 4.7, achieving a Top 10 ranking among hotels in Patong\n• Growing spa revenue by more than 30% through service restructuring and team performance initiatives\n• Implementing the Comanche Property Management System (PMS) across the resort\n• Introducing SARA operational standards across departments to strengthen service consistency\n• Achieving ERTC Green Hotel sustainability certification\n\nPreviously, I led the pre-opening of the 5-star X10 Khaolak Resort (298 rooms), growing annual revenue beyond $9M while increasing average guest spending by 15% through F&B restructuring and guest experience improvements.\n\nI also spent over a decade managing SENTIDO Khao Lak Resort, overseeing 235 rooms while delivering strong guest satisfaction scores (HolidayCheck 92%, OTA 9/10, Google 4.7) and achieving Travelife Gold Certification along with multiple TUI Global Awards.\n\nAcross my career I have led operations for 530+ rooms and teams of over 250 employees, combining operational discipline with a strong focus on guest experience, sustainability, and building high-performing hospitality teams.\n\nI’m passionate about creating service-driven hospitality environments where operational excellence and genuine guest care go hand in hand.", "addressCountryOnly": "Thailand", "addressWithCountry": "Phuket, Thailand", "addressWithoutCountry": "Phuket", "backgroundPic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5616AQGssal1p-ZRNQ/profile-displaybackgroundimage-shrink_350_1400/B56ZtPFUQEHsAc-/0/1766558354362?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=588OEmxjjY4-t6Qpxko-19AvWR42OiIwtgItJqRTq3I", "companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "companyLinkedin": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/andakira-group/", "companyName": "ANDAKIRA GROUP", "companySize": "501-1000", "companyWebsite": "http://www.andakiragroup.com", "connections": "1889", "currentJobDuration": "1 yr 5 mos", "currentJobDurationInYrs": "1.42", "experiences/0/companyId": "13439111", "experiences/0/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/0/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/andakira-group/", "experiences/0/companyName": "ANDAKIRA GROUP", "experiences/0/companySize": "501-1000", "experiences/0/companyUrn": "urn:li:fsd_company:13439111", "experiences/0/companyWebsite": "http://www.andakiragroup.com", "experiences/0/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/0/jobDescription": "General Manager – Crest Resort & Pool Villas, Phuket\n\n• Led overall operations of a 144-room luxury resort including three dining venues and spa facilities, delivering measurable improvements in guest satisfaction and financial performance.\n\n• Increased F&B revenue by 10% year-on-year through refreshed dining concepts and strategic repositioning of outlets.\n\n• Grew spa revenue by 125% year-on-year by introducing new treatments, targeted guest promotions, and incentive-driven staff engagement programs.\n\n• Improved overall operational efficiency by 15% through process optimisation and stronger cross-department coordination.\n\n• Advanced sustainability initiatives toward Green Leaf certification, implementing waste reduction programs, plastic elimination initiatives, and long-term environmental practices.\n\n• Directed the development of a custom hotel operations application to streamline work orders, housekeeping workflows, and front office service requests.\n\n• Led the upgrade of the CRM system, strengthening guest engagement, increasing repeat business, and improving direct booking share.\n\n• Implemented performance-linked incentive programs across Spa, F&B, and Front Office teams to align staff motivation with revenue growth and service excellence.\n\n• Improved Booking.com review score from 8.1 to 8.6 through service culture initiatives, enhanced training, and stronger guest feedback management.", "experiences/0/jobLocation": "Phuket, Thailand", "experiences/0/jobLocationCountry": "TH", "experiences/0/jobStartedOn": "12-2024", "experiences/0/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/0/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQE4pydwB5y9wQ/company-logo_400_400/company-logo_400_400/0/1631325650942?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=KuZlXaJEaxfCtaVPdszCEzbhoGN2rk8Ju7GQwxrNW1M", "experiences/0/title": "General Manager", "experiences/1/companyName": "X10 Khaolak Resort", "experiences/1/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/1/jobDescription": "• Led the pre-opening and operational launch of a 298-room five-star beachfront resort, establishing operational systems, staffing structures, and service standards for a property generating $9M+ annual revenue.\n\n• Directed full resort operations including 2 restaurants, 3 bars, spa, kids club, fitness centre and business facilities, ensuring consistent service delivery across all departments.\n\n• Managed and developed a team of 250+ employees, implementing leadership development programs that reduced staff turnover by 10%.\n\n• Increased average guest spending by 15% through strategic restructuring of F&B concepts and improved guest experience initiatives.\n\n• Maintained strong guest satisfaction ratings across major platforms:\n\t•\tOTAs: 9.1 / 10\n\t•\tHolidayCheck: 91%\n\t•\tGoogle Reviews: 4.7 / 5\n\n• Led resort sustainability initiatives including the elimination of single-use plastics and achieving Travelife Gold Certification.", "experiences/1/jobEndedOn": "1-2025", "experiences/1/jobLocation": "Khao Lak", "experiences/1/jobStartedOn": "7-2016", "experiences/1/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/1/title": "Resort Manager (GM-Equivalent)", "experiences/2/companyName": "SENTIDO Khao Lak", "experiences/2/employmentType": "Full-time", "experiences/2/jobDescription": "• Directed full resort operations for a 235-room beachfront resort, overseeing restaurants, bars, spa facilities and all guest service departments.\n\n• Led the successful brand transition from TUI Blue to SENTIDO, repositioning the property from an adults-only concept to a family-focused resort, including operational restructuring and service redesign.\n\n• Increased annual resort revenue to $6M+ while maintaining strong operational performance and high guest satisfaction standards.\n\n• Maintained strong guest satisfaction scores across key platforms:\n\t•\tHolidayCheck: 92%\n\t•\tOTA average: 9 / 10\n\t•\tGoogle Reviews: 4.7 / 5\n\n• Reduced employee turnover by 15% through leadership development, staff engagement initiatives, and improved team culture.\n\n• Achieved Travelife Gold Sustainability Certification and received multiple TUI Global Awards recognising guest satisfaction and operational excellence.", "experiences/2/jobEndedOn": "1-2025", "experiences/2/jobLocation": "Khao Lak, Thailand", "experiences/2/jobStartedOn": "1-2013", "experiences/2/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/2/title": "Resort Manager (GM-Equivalent)", "experiences/3/companyName": "Thalang